The paper deals with shared autonomy systems, which involve the interaction between an autonomous controller and a human operator. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a policy synthesis algorithm for generating Pareto efficient coordination and control policies, which involves optimization and decision-making. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Furthermore, the paper considers the evolution of the operator's cognitive state during control execution, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses multi-objective optimization methods, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
